summary: Back in November 2017, I kept hearing voices in my head, screaming at me to kill myself over and over again. The feeling was so...
body:
Back in November 2017, I kept hearing voices in my head, screaming at me to kill myself over and over again. The feeling was so strong that I had to run to the toilet at my office to cry. Honestly, it was scary and I was just… REALLY tired.

I was tired of fighting my own battle. I was tired of feeling alone when I’m around my friends and family. I was tired of hating myself. I was tired of not being good enough. I was tired of crying every night until I’m not able to sleep. I was tired to keep a facade to hide my feelings every single day. I was tired of crying for no reason. I was tired of feeling pain.

I looked at the window at my apartment at that time. I wanted to jump. I wanted to end the pain. I wanted to give up.

But, within the screams in my head, I could hear tiny voices that said, “Help! Help me! Somebody help me!” In that moment, I knew I had to seek help and I’m glad I did.

All the photographs posted here are original work from photographers I follow  on tumblr . My aim is  twofold, share the inspiration, and give photographers a bit more exposure .     
 I am also part of the  Lux Lit  team of rebloggers, and ms-excuse me with Thierry Facon, where the main focus is to bring you lesser known photographs that we feel deserve some more attention. 
 Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions or comments, or would  like me to check out your blog;  I'm on a constant quest for new photography blogs to follow .
